</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="596" pageNumber="597" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="596.[151,1437,369,1115]" pageId="596" pageNumber="597">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,369,396]" pageId="596" pageNumber="597">Description.</emphasis>
<specimenCount box="[353,374,370,396]" pageId="596" pageNumber="597" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
(
<figureCitation box="[391,515,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURE 266" captionStartId="594.[151,250,1226,1251]" captionTargetBox="[157,1405,194,1198]" captionTargetId="figure@594.[151,1436,174,1214]" captionTargetPageId="594" captionText="FIGURE 266. Habitus of Apoaphelopus species. A–C: A. mostovskii Olmi: ♂ holotype in dorsal (A) and lateral (C) view; ♂ from South Africa, 31°12.923’S 19°40.812’E, in dorsal view (B). D: A. wallacei Olmi, Copeland &amp; van Noort sp. nov.: ♂ holo- type in dorsal view. Scale bar: A: 1.20 mm; B: 1.56 mm; C: 0.78 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337210/files/figure.png" pageId="596" pageNumber="597">Figs 266D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[527,573,369,396]" captionStart="FIGURE 267" captionStartId="595.[151,250,1944,1969]" captionTargetBox="[183,1417,501,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@595.[151,1436,481,1932]" captionTargetPageId="595" captionText="FIGURE 267. Apoaphelopus wallacei Olmi, Copeland &amp; van Noort sp. nov., ♂ holotype: habitus in dorsal (A) and lateral (B) view; mesosoma in dorsal (C) and lateral (D) view; head in frontal view (E); forewing (F)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337212/files/figure.png" pageId="596" pageNumber="597">267</figureCitation>
). Fully winged; length 
<quantity box="[840,931,369,396]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="596" pageNumber="597" unit="mm" value="0.9">0.9 mm</quantity>
. Head testaceous-dark, except mandible tes- taceous; antenna whitish; mesosoma and metasoma testaceous; legs yellow-testaceous. Antenna filiform, shorter than body; antennomeres in following proportions: 7:3:2:2.5:2.5:3:2.5:2:2:5. Head convex, subspheroidal, dull, granulate, finely setose; occiput very concave, unsculptured; frontal line absent; central area of frons with slight short median longitudinal furrow; occipital carina complete; POL = 3; OL = 1.5; OOL = 1.5; TL = 1; posterior ocelli touching occipital carina; temple shorter than eye (1:5). Mesoscutum, mesoscutellum and metanotum shiny, completely unsculptured. Notauli incomplete, reaching about 0.5 × length of mesoscutum. Epicnemium exposed. Metapectal-propodeal disc and propodeal declivity shiny, almost completely unsculptured, slightly rugose on sides of metapectal-propodeal disc. Mesopleuron and metapleuron shiny, unsculptured. Forewing without pterostigma, with costal vein very thick; costal cell absent; 2r-rs&amp;Rs vein present and not reaching margin of forewing; other veins of forewing absent, veins M and Cu being marked by dark stripes. Hind wing with costal vein absent, with two dark longitudinal median stripes. Basivolsella (
<figureCitation box="[680,792,765,792]" captionStart="FIGURE 264" captionStartId="590.[151,250,1869,1894]" captionTargetBox="[167,1384,837,1830]" captionTargetId="figure@590.[151,1436,827,1858]" captionTargetPageId="590" captionText="FIGURE 264. A, B: Vannoortia capensis Olmi, ♂ holotype: mesosoma in ventral view (A; M = mesosternum); genitalia (B). C–F: ♂ genitalia of Apoaphelopus species holotypes: C: A. fisheri Olmi, Copeland &amp; van Noort sp. nov.; D: A. mostovskii Olmi; E: A. niassensis Olmi; F: A. wallacei Olmi, Copeland &amp; van Noort sp. nov. Scale bar: A: 0.43 mm; B: 0.09 mm; C: 0.05 mm; D: 0.06 mm; E: 0.08 mm; F: 0.04 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337206/files/figure.png" pageId="596" pageNumber="597">Fig. 264F</figureCitation>
) with distal process parallel to distivolsella. Palpi absent. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
